definition.value: A carbocyclic fatty acid that is hexanoic acid substituted at position 6 by a 3-oxo-2-{(Z)-pent-2-en-1-yl}cyclopentyl group.
A galactosyl disaccharide group formed by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-alpha-D-galactose.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function of 3-methyldeoxyadenosine 5'-monophosphate residue; major species at pH 7.3.
A purine deoxyribonucleotide residue derived from N(6)-methyl-2'-deoxyadenosine 5'-monophosphate

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phosphophytoceramide(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phospho-N-acylphytosphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phosphophytoceramide(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phospho-C20-phytoceramide; major species at pH 7.3.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phosphodihydroceramide(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phospho-N-acylsphinganine; major species at pH 7.3.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phosphodihydroceramide(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the free phosphate OH group of inositol phosphomannosylinositol-1-phospho-C20-dihydroceramide; major species at pH 7.3.
A deoxyribonucleotide residue that has lost its base either spontaneously or through the action of glycosylases.
An organic anionic group that is the conjugate base of 2'-deoxyribose 5'-monophosphate residue obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group; major species at pH 7.3.
A zwitterionic group derived from 1-methyldeoxyadenosine  5'-monophosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
A zwitterionic group derived from 7-methyldeoxyguanosine 5'-monophosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

A beta-D-galactosyl disaccharide group formed by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactose. Implied reactive epitope within lactosylceramide.
A beta-D-galactosyl disaccharide group formed by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactose.
A member of the class of  benzodioxoles that is 1,3-benzodioxole substituted by a 2-(methylamino)propyl group at position 5.

A disaccharide consisting of beta-D-galactopyranose having a D-galactopyranosyl residue attached at the 6-position via an alpha-linkage. alpha-D-Gal-(1->6)-D-Gal in which the configuration at the reducing end anomeric centre is beta.
A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose
A glycosyl group obtained by removing the hydroxy group from the hemiacetal function of alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->2)-[alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)]-beta-D-galactose
A branched trisaccharide comprising beta-D-galactose (at the reducing end), to which are linked (1->2) and (1->6) alpha-D-galactosyl residues.
A 3-hydroxydecanoyl-3-hydroxydecanoate resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of (R,R)-3-(3-hydroxydecanoyloxy)decanoic acid. The major species at pH 7.3.
An oxo fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxylic acid group of (9S,13S)-1a,1b-dinor-10,11-dihydro-12-oxo-15-phytoenoic acid.
A synthetic alpha-galactosylsphingamide in which the galactose ring carries a (2S,3S,4R)-3,4-dihydroxy-2-(octanoylamino)-8-oxo-8-[(6-phenylhexyl)amino]octyl moiety at O-1.
An oxo fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxylic acid group of (9S,13S)-1a,1b-dinor-12-oxo-10,15-phytodienoic acid.
An acyl monophosphate in which the acyl group is specified as hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl).
An agonist that activates IP3 receptors.
A 3-hydroxydecanoyl-3-hydroxydecanoic acid in which both stereocentres have R configuration.
A galactolipid in which the side chain of a galactosylphytosphingosine has been modified by amidation. Some alpha-galactosylsphingamides have been shown to exhibit antigenic properties.
A synthetic alpha-galactosylsphingamide in which the galactose ring carries a (2S,3S,4R)-3,4-dihydroxy-2-(octanoylamino)-8-oxo-8-[(8-phenyloctyl)amino]octyl moiety at O-1.
A synthetic sphingoid in which C16 phytosphingosine is substituted at O-1, C-16 and N with respectively an alpha-D-galactopyranosyl group, a phenyl group and an octanoyl group.
Any carotenoid derivative with a psi-end group.
Any carotenoid  derivative with an epsilon-end group.
Any carotenoid derivative with an beta-end group
A medium-chain unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3E,5Z)-dodecadienoic acid.
A monoterpenoid indole alkaloid obtained by formal hydration across the 2,3-double bond of tabersonine.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of C-terminal S-carbamoyl-L-cysteine residue; major species at pH 7.3.
An alpha-amino-acid residue anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of C-terminal S-cyano-L-cysteine residue; major species at pH 7.3.

A sulfonamide resulting from the formal condensation of the sulfonic acid group of 2-oxo-1,2-dihydroquinoline-6-sulfonic acid with the primary amino group of (2R)-2-amino-N-(2-furylmethyl)-2-(2-methoxyphenyl)-N-(2-thienylmethyl)acetamide. OSMI-1 is a cell permeable inhibitor of O-linked beta-N-acetylglucosamine transferase (O-GlcNAc transferase, OGT).

A galactosylceramide sulfate(1-) that is the conjugate base of 1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-N-[(15Z)-tetracos-15-enoyl]sphingosine obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate group; major species at pH 7.3.
